From: Andrew Jones <drjones@redhat.com>
Date: Wed, 11 May 2016 21:23:17 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 050/147] irqchip/gic-v3: Fix quiescence check in
 gic_enable_redist

Git-commit: cf1d9d11e25053a264c0001aa86be7680bb1ecc1
Patch-mainline: v4.7-rc5
References: fate#320512, fate#322061

Make sure the two sides of the bitwise operation are bool.

Signed-off-by: Andrew Jones <drjones@redhat.com>
Signed-off-by: Marc Zyngier <marc.zyngier@arm.com>
Signed-off-by: Mian Yousaf Kaukab <yousaf.kaukab@suse.com>
---
 drivers/irqchip/irq-gic-v3.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/drivers/irqchip/irq-gic-v3.c b/drivers/irqchip/irq-gic-v3.c
index 75ccec9..971671c 100644
--- a/drivers/irqchip/irq-gic-v3.c
+++ b/drivers/irqchip/irq-gic-v3.c
@@ -157,7 +157,7 @@ static void gic_enable_redist(bool enable)
 
 	while (--count) {
 		val = readl_relaxed(rbase + GICR_WAKER);
-		if (enable ^ (val & GICR_WAKER_ChildrenAsleep))
+		if (enable ^ (bool)(val & GICR_WAKER_ChildrenAsleep))
 			break;
 		cpu_relax();
 		udelay(1);
